No, the big fat "normal" 40hp ones with the condensor inside the cap are
vacuum-advance.  The bastard 40hp dizzy is the normal size, just a differ=
ent
Bosch part # and advance curve.  I don't remember the exact Bosch # but
it's in the archives if you search for bastard engine info.

I bought parts for my mechanical distributor from Vintage Parts in CA but=

it was years ago.  For the correct restoration minded people, they don't
sell the original L-style rotors or correct brown-colored dizzy caps, exc=
ept
for when they have a limited supply of NOS units.

